  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile, W-ON-01 probe)",
  "description": "Credibility evidence package for CFD-based hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) operating conditions. The governing regulatory requirement (21 CFR 870.3545) mandates absolute hemolysis prediction accuracy for a Class III implantable device at Model Risk Level 5. The claim asserts that the Eulerian scalar-transport hemolysis model, calibrated against the FDA benchmark dataset, produces normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) predictions within ±25% of in-vitro measurements across the intended VAD flow envelope (3–6 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM). All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors have been addressed; seven were fully assessed and six were scoped under epistemic-gap flags consistent with MRL 5 guidance. Monte Carlo uncertainty propagation (n=2000 samples) was executed to bound input-parameter sensitivity. The decision record reflects acceptance conditional on the stated factor levels and uncertainty bounds. NOTE: this package conforms to ProfileMinimal; the structured hasContextOfUse object is intentionally absent — intended-use scope is described only in this prose field and in the bound Claim and Requirement nodes.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-vad-hemolysis-mrl5-req",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-vad-nih-within-25pct",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/eulerian-hemolysis-cfd-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
